misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No detected misconception (correct arithmetic / operator precedence)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes the trip cost is computed as distance ÷ (miles per gallon) × (price per gallon), and that Java will evaluate the expression left-to-right with * and / having the same precedence.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap: In Java, * and / have the same precedence and are evaluated left-to-right, so (y/n*z) correctly computes (distance / mpg) * pricePerGallon. Using doubles also matches the need for fractional values.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No bug for the given problem; output matches the required calculation (though it prints the raw double without formatting, which is still acceptable given the sample).
